I'm upgrading my rating from a 2 to a 4 due to some improvements in the functioning of the App.  The content information provided by Steve Brill is excellent, but the images download function still has serious problems as of 10-12-17.  First, despite what the App description claims, it actually places the images on the internal phone memory, NOT on the microSD card.  (I experienced this with 2 different brand phones.)  If you can't spare tying up 2.38 GB of your phone's internal memory for the images, I would strongly hesitate purchasing this App as it currently is.  Second, downloading is a total pain with this App (buggy).  Expect to clear the image folders and re-attempt image downloading several times before it will successfully get all the images loaded.  I now finally have a fully functioning App thanks to a high internal memory phone and probably 10 or more image download attempts.  Be persistent.

The bad: Images don't load when swiped to see more. Sometimes they do, but rarely. The UI is clunky and weird, this would be much better if it was just a standard off-the-shelf material design implementation.  The good: - The information within this app is incredible, unparallelled. - The creator of it has found a new developer and is pushing forward with a much better version for all of us.

replyContent:
Hi Ian,
I wasn't able to reproduce the issue you had, but I have a fix that might work. In your file manager program, delete the WildEdiblesImages/ folder completely, and then come back to the app and run the downloader again. I feel like something might've gone wrong during download. Let me know if that works!

This app by "Wildman" Steve Brill and friends is an incredibely helpful resource outdoors in the search for highly nutritious wild edibles.    Steve is a vast wealth of information, stories and jokes in person that make wild foraging fun and easy to learn.   This app filled with very clear photos and descriptions of identification is so easy to use and the next best thing to taking a tour with a very experienced forager.   The app also includes delicious recipes for each wild edible!
ok.

The Wild Edible app is nearly as informative as the AUTHOR Steve Brill in person.  But of course nothing can replace the family friendly corny jokes and anecdotes. This has been my go to source of valuable ethnobotanical information and serves as the perfect companion and memory jogger after attending one of the "Wildmans" Urban wilderness excursions, since one can barely absorb the wealth of information he presents in person. The photos are clear and representative of the plant species discussed. The drop down menu format makes everything seem very tidy and indexed.  My only complaint is that there should be alot more recipes since just looking at the app makes me hungry for some really Wild Edibles.  I cant wait for the updates.  Keep up the good work Professor Wildman!
Please keep updating with more information love all the detailed pics

content: Very well organized, good info and photos with no unnecessary fluff. Steve Brill was wonderful to get back to me with unrelated question. This is the first, and probably only, review I write: I usually don't bother, but this App was worth the time to type on phone keyboard :)

This app has provided countless hours of enjoyment, a much better alternative to video games when one has some free time on the subway, etc. Lots of useful information to help identify and prepare wild edibles. While not a replacement for the book or others like it, it is a useful supplement to the reading material. Worth the purchase!

This app is the best I've seen for beginner and intermediate foragers.  What I like best is that many of the plants have several photos so you can see how it looks close up and in the field.  The quality of some of the photos isn't great, but all in all, I consider the app superb.  I also like that you can select the "Image" view and view them like flash cards.

While this book is most applicable to the Northeast region, it has a very friendly interface, excellent illustrations and tasty recipes that show real thought and experience working with the ingredients. Whether you're just getting started with foraging or more experienced and looking for unique ideas on what to do with wild foods, this app will prove worthy of your attention.

Great app!  Full of great information not only for identifying edibles but their medicinal uses as well!  Thanks for compiling all this information so concisely.  This is well worth the money and beats carrying a bulky field guide into the woods.

App is time consuming to navigate. When reading up on a plant, you constantly have to be going back to the menu to choose the next section. Example. Using > Harvesting (back) Food Use (back) Nutrition (back) etc. Should be able to swipe right / left for next section, or simply list them all and scroll through since then are often just a few lines long. Great content, but much more detail in his books. Photos are the only benefit of app, otherwise just get the digital book.
replyContent: Hello Brian! We've updated the app to have a new interface - and better organizational structure. If you can update we'd love to hear your feedback on this new version.

I want to state upfront that my review is not for the content and information within this app, which I think is excellent and I highly recommend, Steve Brill is very knowledgable and has years of experience with leading foraging tours. My review is for the app itself.  I originally downloaded the free lite version to my Kindle fire and I loved it, worked great, so I decided to pay for the full version of this app and to my surprise, it wasnt available for the Kindle fire.  Im not sure why you would make the free version available and not the full paid version.  But since my phone is an android device I decided to buy it anyway and download it to my phone.  After paying and downloading the full version to my phone I noticed there was a lot of missing information.  Almost all of the poisonous plant links were either unavailable or the links were broken.  Many of the plants that had cautions were completely missing information under the cautions section (even though its there in the lite version).  I would have given 5 stars if the app wasnt missing info and its available for kindle fire hdx.  Please update the paid version and I would be happy to update my review and give 5 stars!!!

I just purchased this app but I immediately had a few issues with it. First, plants should be sortable by habitat or range as well as name. Not all plants are available in all areas. Second, there are multiple formatting/spelling issues. For example, when I select certain plants, I'm told that there is a poisonous lookalike. I can see a list of them, but selecting one brings up a placeholder page with no image or information. I'm less likely to attempt collecting this plant if I can't compare it to its poisonous lookalike. However, it's a good start so I'm going to hang on to this app in hopes that it improves.

If you would like to try updating, we think you'll find that this version of the app is much better.

content: Developer never read and reply to email
replyContent: Hello Daeseop, So sorry for not responding. We are a small company (just two people!) and sometimes things fall through the cracks. We have (finally) updated the app to a new version and if you would like to update I think you'll find that this version works much better. If not we are also now able to answer your concerns.

content: Very glad I purchased this.  I immediately was able to positively I.D. four edible plants growing around my work parking lot. I've had it for a few weeks and use it frequently.  Well designed and encyclopedic in depth, it demonstrates the possibilities of the technology.  Hard  to imagine anything surpassing this app for people with a genuine interest in wild foods.

This application is one of the reasons for actually owning an android device! The pictures are very illustrative of the plants' identifying features. The ones that are covered are comprehensive and representative of their utility to the forager and naturalist. I have owned a number of books on wild edibles and have always had difficulty identifying a plant in the field via a picture in a book. This guide somehow manages to make this task much easier. Thank you Wildman for giving us the opportunity to enjoy this activity like never before possible.
This is a great resource for the trail.  I would like to have a feature that allows you to check off edibles you have found so you can mark it off the list.

This app is wonderful for foragers who want to expand their knowledge while out on the trail.  It doesn't need network access, so you can quickly look up plants to double check your identification and find uses you hadn't thought of yet. I like the recipes too.  I have found that it crashes when left open after the phone sleeps, but you can just close and reopen it.
Love this app. Very helpful
App did not work at all
Love the wild man! App is like a foraging book right on your phone! Lots of pics, and new updates. Can't wait for our next foraging class with him, we had a blast!
Steve Brill is and has been a leader in wild edible education for years.  Thanks for pairing a great educational tool and new technology.  Thanks Steve for all the years of great information.
Love this app, very useful, a definite must have!!!!

As a wild food lover (but not an expert) I find this app to be so useful as I go out and seek out new plants to identify.  I always have my phone but not always my books. This app has a lot of details for each plant. Easy to use too.
I could not open it at all :(
Great App!

I have never purchased an ap, I always just use the free versions. However, after playing with the free version of this, I had to have the extended, full ap! I tried other, similar aps and none of them came close! Excellent resource!

I love your app on my Ipad and my smart phone!! Everyone should have one!! Great close up photos full color, and so much information. Everything from poisonous look alikes to recipes . Valuable tool in the field and the back yard! Thank you

Over 150 plants in detail, w/ several photos. Photos of poisonous look a likes. Very descriptive. Shows ways to prepare and lists medicinal properties. Over half the plants grow as far south east as south Florida. Very pleased.

Easy to use, accurate and very helpful to identify plants in the field. The occasional bit  of  humor is a great treat, even if it causes some groans. Great for beginners as well as experienced wildcrafters.

Created by a leading authority in the world of foraging, this app brings both sage knowledge, clear pictures and descriptions, with wit humor and fun. A must-have cutting-edge resource for The New [Green] Age!

Wildman has thoroughly researched the plants and their uses. Best of all, he tries out the plants and gives practical advice about the work necessary and the results--is the food worth the effort for the flavor and food value.  A true professional.  Too bad about his sense of humor, though.
Love it.....need more!!!
A taxonomy key would be nice but I can see how it might be too much work. But what this map really needs are maps of the plants range

This app is so great that I bought it for my iPhone, and it was one of the first apps I bought again when I switched to Droid.  Steve Brill is the ultimate foraging teacher.  The photography in this app is clear and just perfect, so the plants are easily recognizable.  I'm hoping he'll add even more plants to the app as time goes by.  My ONLY complaint is some junk text in the Welcome statement.

The content here is great, and well presented.  It has come in handy many times for me, and the advantage of having this info with me at all times is substantial. The app has a few issues with polish, though, and generally needs a bit more technical attention.
I had the pleasure of speaking with Mr. Brill and will be attending one of his tours very soon!  Can't wait! I'll be using the app for the tour!

One of this biggest problems that prevented me from foraging was I never seemed to have my books with me when I stumbled upon a plant that I suspected was edible. This app has made that a thing of the past. The navigation is pretty intuitive and there is some room for improvement, but I find the pictures are excellent and the information about dangerous lookalikes is very comforting. Keep up the good work Steve!
It's exactly what I was looking for!
I used this app to forage in Prospect Park.  Having both the photos and the illustrations of each plant made them easy to identify.  The recipe ideas are a nice bonus.
Very intuitive and helpful.  Searching for the identity of something is much easier with 3 pictures for each plant and a "similar plants" software option.
Brilliant app gives me confidence to forrage safely. Love it, been wanting something like this for a while!

I have been on the hunt for wild foods and have done my share of foraging since I became interested in this topic after reading Euell Gibbons Book 'Stalking the Wild Asparagus' in the early 70's.  Now there's no more lugging around heavy books to try and identify a wild food - Wild Man Steve Brills app makes the hunt sooooo much easier! -Jim McGowan, Bucks County, PA
Force close when tap common elderberry picture
Amazing app! We've been going out foraging twice a week after attending two of Steve's classes, and this app has made everything so much easier. Thanks, Steve!

As a somewhat newbie to the wonderful world of foraging, I really appreciate both the wisdom and the humor in this app.  It has really helped me out and about and as a cross-reference, as well as with recipe ideas. Thank you!
There is so much information yet it is easy to use. I have a number of foraging books including those by the "Wild Man." I now have a great reference with me at all times.
Cool stuff.
If you want to learn about wild edible plants and a little about there medicinal uses then buy this.  The app could be better,  but hopefully the devs will update it.
App is exactly what I was looking for. If could search plants by areas, would give 5 stars.

The screen is the size of an iPhone. I have a 4.3" screen and it uses 3/4 of it. The info is good but I'd like to have the ability to add notes to the plants. I know recipes that aren't listed and it would be great to add them on my personal app. More search functions would be nice too. Like "by flavor"(sweet, spicy,  bitter, etc.) And "by medicinal properties" ( symptoms, properties, etc.)

I own his book and have been on a few of his tours. This app is full of well-organized information. If in the future it gets integrated social networking, I might rate out at 5 stars. There are a few typos, and some of the photos should be resized so they don't get stretched out. But overall I highly recommend this app.
Perfect w tons of info & photos - thanks, Wild Man Steve!!!
This is exactly what I was looking for so handy to have on a phone. Very user friendly looking forward to learning about local plants.
